{"title_page": "Savannah James", "text_new": "{{short description|American businesswoman and philanthropist and wife of Basketball player Lebron James}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Savannah James\n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Savannah Brinson\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1986|08|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Akron, Ohio]]\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = Businesswoman\n| years_active       = \n| spouse             = [[LeBron James]] (m. 2013)\n| children           = 3 \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n}}\n\n'''Savannah James''' ([[n\u00e9e]] '''Brinson'''; born August 27, 1986) is an American businesswoman and philanthropist.<ref name=\"essencemagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Charreah |title=Savannah James On Married Life With LeBron, Why She's So Private On Social Media and Her Incredible Year |url=https://www.essence.com/love-sex/lebron-james-wife-savannah-james-motherhood-marriage-balance |publisher=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nSavannah Brinson was born to Jennifer and JK Brinson. Brinson met [[LeBron James]] while attending [[Buchtel Community Learning Center]].<ref name=\"clevelandmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Thompson |first1=Lynne |title=Most Interesting People 2018: Savannah James |url=https://clevelandmagazine.com/in-the-cle/the-read/articles/most-interesting-people-2018-savannah-james |publisher=[[Cleveland Magazine]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"businessinsider\">{{cite web |last1=Cain |first1=Aine |title=LeBron James first met his wife Savannah in high school |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/lebron-james-marriage-wife-savannah-2017-11 |publisher=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2018, James started a furniture line with [[American Signature]] called ''Home Court''.<ref name=\"entitymagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Hoye |first1=Kyleigh |title=Savannah Brinson: Five Fun Facts About Lebron James's Wife |url=http://www.entitymag.com/samantha-brinson-five-facts-lebrons-wife/ |publisher=Entity Magazine |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> She also founded a mentorship program called ''Women of Our Future''.<ref name=\"clevelandmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Thompson |first1=Lynne |title=Most Interesting People 2018: Savannah James |url=https://clevelandmagazine.com/in-the-cle/the-read/articles/most-interesting-people-2018-savannah-james |publisher=[[Cleveland Magazine]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> In 2016, James provided local Akron high school senior students with prom dresses.<ref name=\"foxsports\">{{cite web |title=LeBron James' wife helps high school students make prom dream come true |url=https://www.foxsports.com/nba/story/lebron-james-wife-savannah-james-prom-promise-makeover-dresses-041016 |publisher=[[Fox Sports]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> James also owned a juice store, ''The Juice Shop'', in [[Brickell, Florida]], but closed it in 2016 due to moving back to Ohio.<ref name=\"miaminewtimes\">{{cite web |last1=Munzenrieder |first1=Kyle |title=LeBron James' Wife to Shut Down Her Brickell Juice Caf\u00e9 |url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/lebron-james-wife-to-shut-down-her-brickell-juice-caf-8154870 |publisher=[[Miami New Times]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBasketball player LeBron James proposed to Savannah, his high school sweetheart, at a December 31, 2011 party celebrating New Year's Eve and his 27th birthday.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/jan/01/sports/la-sp-newswire-20120102|title=LeBron James and Savannah Brinson are engaged|work=Los Angeles Times|author=Wire Reports|date=January 1, 2012|accessdate=January 2, 2012}}</ref> The two were married on September 14, 2013 in [[San Diego, California]].<ref>{{cite web|title=LEBRON WEDS GIRLFRIEND IN SAN DIEGO|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/ap-source-lebron-weds-girlfriend-san-diego|publisher=AP|accessdate=September 15, 2013}}</ref> Together, they have three children.<ref>{{cite web|title=LeBron James Fast Facts|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/07/07/sport/lebron-james-fast-facts/|publisher=CNN|accessdate=August 18, 2014|author=CNN Library}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{LeBron James}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:James, Savannah}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American women in business]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Akron, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Philanthropists from Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American businesswoman and philanthropist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Savannah James\n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Savannah Brinson\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1986|08|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Akron, Ohio]]\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = Businesswoman\n| years_active       = \n| spouse             = [[LeBron James]] (m. 2013)\n| children           = 3 \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n}}\n\n'''Savannah James''' ([[n\u00e9e]] '''Brinson'''; born August 27, 1986) is an American businesswoman and philanthropist.<ref name=\"essencemagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Charreah |title=Savannah James On Married Life With LeBron, Why She's So Private On Social Media and Her Incredible Year |url=https://www.essence.com/love-sex/lebron-james-wife-savannah-james-motherhood-marriage-balance |publisher=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nSavannah Brinson was born to Jennifer and JK Brinson. Brinson met [[LeBron James]] while attending [[Buchtel Community Learning Center]].<ref name=\"clevelandmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Thompson |first1=Lynne |title=Most Interesting People 2018: Savannah James |url=https://clevelandmagazine.com/in-the-cle/the-read/articles/most-interesting-people-2018-savannah-james |publisher=[[Cleveland Magazine]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"businessinsider\">{{cite web |last1=Cain |first1=Aine |title=LeBron James first met his wife Savannah in high school |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/lebron-james-marriage-wife-savannah-2017-11 |publisher=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2018, James started a furniture line with [[American Signature]] called ''Home Court''.<ref name=\"entitymagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Hoye |first1=Kyleigh |title=Savannah Brinson: Five Fun Facts About Lebron James's Wife |url=http://www.entitymag.com/samantha-brinson-five-facts-lebrons-wife/ |publisher=Entity Magazine |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> She also founded a mentorship program called ''Women of Our Future''.<ref name=\"clevelandmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Thompson |first1=Lynne |title=Most Interesting People 2018: Savannah James |url=https://clevelandmagazine.com/in-the-cle/the-read/articles/most-interesting-people-2018-savannah-james |publisher=[[Cleveland Magazine]] |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref> In 2016, James provided local Akron high school senior students with prom dresses.<ref name=\"foxsports\">{{cite web |title=LeBron James' wife helps high school students make prom dream come true |url=https://www.