-  style=\"background:#ddd; text-align:center;\"\n| FB || [[Kris Wilson (American football)|Kris Wilson]] || UFA || March 26 || [[Philadelphia Eagles]] ||\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<small>''RFA'': [[Restricted free agent]], ''UFA'': [[Unrestricted free agent]], ''ERFA'': Exclusive rights free agent</small>\n|}\n\n====Additions====\nIn February, Kansas City claimed OT [[Anthony Alabi]] off waivers from the Miami Dolphins.<ref>[http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/02/13/kansas_city_claims_t_anthony_alabi_off_waivers/ Kansas City claims T Anthony Alabi off waivers] ''KCChiefs.com'', February 13, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080217180042/http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/02/13/kansas_city_claims_t_anthony_alabi_off_waivers/ |date=February 17, 2008 }}</ref> Kansas City also agreed to two-year contracts with K [[Nick Novak]], S [[Erick Harris]], DT [[T.J. Jackson (defensive tackle)|T.J. Jackson]], CB [[Chad Johnson (cornerback)|Chad Johnson]], OT [[Joe Lobdell]], and G [[Rob Smith (American football)|Rob Smith]].<ref name=\"Cundiff\">Associated Press. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3252250 Chiefs ink kicker Cundiff to two-year deal] ''ESPN.com'', February 18, 2008.</ref>\n\nIn March, Kansas City claimed FB [[Oliver Hoyte]] off waivers from the Dallas Cowboys.<ref>[http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/03/kansas_city_claims_fb_oliver_hoyte_off_waivers/ Kansas City claims FB Oliver Hoyte off waivers] ''KCChiefs.com'', March 3, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080306163236/http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/03/kansas_city_claims_fb_oliver_hoyte_off_waivers/ |date=March 6, 2008 }}</ref> The team also signed free agent LB [[Demorrio Williams]],<ref>[http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/03/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_ufa_lb_demorrio_williams/ Kansas City agrees to terms with UFA LB Demorrio Williams] ''KCChiefs.com'', March 3, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080305160143/http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/03/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_ufa_lb_demorrio_williams/ |date=March 5, 2008 }}</ref> and WR [[Devard Darling]].<ref name=\"Darling\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/11/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_wr_devard_darling/ Chiefs agree to terms with WR Devard Darling] ''KCChiefs.com'', March 11, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080314234128/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/03/11/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_wr_devard_darling/ |date=March 14, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn April, Kansas City signed KR [[B. J. Sams (American football)|B.J. Sams]], TE [[John Paul Foschi]]<ref name=\"Foschi\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/16/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_fb_john_paul_foschi/ Kansas City agrees to terms with FB John Paul Foschi] ''KCChiefs.com'', April 16, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418071640/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/16/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_fb_john_paul_foschi/ |date=April 18, 2008 }}</ref> and C [[Wade Smith]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2008/04/21/sports/FBN-Chiefs-Smith.php|title=Chiefs sign unrestricted free agent Wade Smith|agency=Associated Press|publisher=The Herald Tribune|accessdate=April 22, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn May, the Chiefs signed a total of 23 [[Undrafted sportsperson|undrafted free agents]].<ref name=\"17 rookie\">[http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/02/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_17_rookie_free_agents/ Chiefs agree to terms with 17 rookie free agents] ''KCChiefs.com'', May 2, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080609051905/http://www.kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/02/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_17_rookie_free_agents/ |date=June 9, 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\"Six Rookie\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/20/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_six_rookie_free_agents/ Chiefs agree to terms with six rookie free agents] ''KCChiefs.com'', May 20, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080531014702/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/20/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_six_rookie_free_agents/ |date=May 31, 2008 }}</ref> and cornerbacks [[Will Poole]] and [[Jason Horton]].<ref name=\"Poole, Horton\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/27/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_two_free_agent_cornerbacks/ Kansas City agrees to terms with two free agent cornerbacks] ''KCChiefs.com'', May 27, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080529225449/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/05/27/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_two_free_agent_cornerbacks/ |date=May 29, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn August, the Chiefs signed K [[Jay Feely]] but released him the following day.\n\nIn September, the Chiefs signed QB [[Ingle Martin]] following an injury to [[Brodie Croyle]].<ref name=\"Ingle Martin leaving Titans for Chiefs\">{{cite web|url=http://tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080909/SPORTS01/80909093/1002/SPORTS|title=Ingle Martin leaving Titans for Chiefs|last=Wyatt|first=Jim|date=September 10, 2008|publisher=Tennessean.com|accessdate=September 10, 2008}} {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn October, the Chiefs re-signed K [[Connor Barth]], who was released at the beginning of the season at the 53-man roster deadline.<ref name=\"change kickers\">{{cite news | title=Chiefs change kickers, search for a QB | url=http://www.kfvs12.com/Global/story.asp?S=9215150&nav=menu51_4 | agency=Associated Press | work=KFVS | date=October 21, 2008 | accessdate=October 21, 2008}}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Kansas City also signed QB [[Quinn Gray]] following a season-ending injury to starting QB [[Brodie Croyle]].<ref>[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/10/22/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_qb_quinn_gray/ Chiefs agree to terms with QB Quinn Gray] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081025053933/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/10/22/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_qb_quinn_gray/ |date=October 25, 2008 }} ''Kansas City Chiefs official website'', October 22, 2008.</ref> A slew of injuries to the Chiefs' starting lineup in October and November made the team sign several players in order to fill holes.<ref name=\"Interesting list\"/><ref name=\"Bruised\">{{cite web | title=Bruised, Battered and Bewildered | url=http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/11/12/bruised_battered_and_bewildered/ | archive-url=https://archive.today/20110713141928/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/11/12/bruised_battered_and_bewildered/ | url-status=dead | archive-date=July 13, 2011 | last=Gretz | first=Bob | work=Kansas City Chiefs official website | date=November 12, 2008 | accessdate=November 14, 2008}}</ref>\n\n====Departures====\nIn February, the Chiefs released WR [[Eddie Kennison]],<ref name=\"Chiefs cut loose\">Associated Press. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3266120 Chiefs cut loose former top starting wideout Kennison] ''ESPN.com'', February 26, 2008.</ref> OT [[John Welbourn]],<ref name=\"Welbourn\"/> RB [[Gilbert Harris]],<ref name=\"Welbourn\"/> DE [[Khreem Smith]],<ref name=\"Welbourn\"/> CB [[Ty Law]],<ref name=\"Bell, Dunn\">Associated Press. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3267558 Report: Chiefs to release Bell, Dunn, Law, Reed] ''ESPN.com'', February 27, 2008.</ref> LB [[Kendrell Bell]],<ref name=\"Bell, Dunn\"/> TE [[Jason Dunn (American football)|Jason Dunn]],<ref name=\"Bell, Dunn\"/> DT [[James Reed (American football)|James Reed]],<ref name=\"Bell, Dunn\"/> and OT [[Chris Bober]].<ref name=\"Chiefs resign Colquitt\">[http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3269418&campaign=rss&source=NFLHeadlines Chiefs resign Colquitt, but Law likely to be cut] ''ESPN.com'', February 29, 2008.</ref> After attempting to trade him for the second consecutive year, the Chiefs released FS [[Greg Wesley]] in July.<ref name=\"Wesley agreees\">Williamson, Bill. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3500590 Wesley agrees to one-year, $730K contract with Raiders] ''ESPN.com'', July 22, 2008.</ref> In October, Kansas City released LB [[Napoleon Harris]],<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3646811 Injury-depleted Vikings agree to deal with Harris, agent confirms 16 October 2008.]</ref> and K [[Nick Novak]].<ref name=\"change kickers\"/>\n\n====Failed signings====\nThe Chiefs were as aggressive as NFL rules allowed them to be in pursuing of C [[Jeff Faine]] and K [[Josh Brown (American football)|Josh Brown]], both of whom signed with teams on the first day of free agency.<ref name=\"Bucs, Rams\">[http://www.fannation.com/truth_and_rumors/view/44400 Bucs, Rams anger Edwards] ''Kansas City Star'', March 25, 2008.</ref> NFL rules prohibit teams from contacting prospective free agents or their agents until free agency begins.<ref name=\"Bucs, Rams\"/> In 2008, that time was 11&nbsp;p.m. on February 28.<ref name=\"Bucs, Rams\"/> \"There were probably some deals done before (the start of the league year)\", Edwards said when asked why the Chiefs didn't get in the game with either player. \"We didn't cheat. We abided by the rules. That's how you're supposed to do it, and that's what we did.\"<ref name=\"Bucs, Rams\"/>\n\nEntering the season, the Chiefs were unsure if injury-prone [[Brodie Croyle]] could be their quarterback of the future.<ref name=\"Several '08\">{{cite web | title=Several '08 picks should make immediate impact | url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/columns/story?columnist=williamson_bill&id=3448409 | last=Williamson | first=Bill | publisher=ESPN.com | date=June 18, 2008 | accessdate=December 21, 2008}}</ref> Following the season-ending injury to QB Croyle, the Chiefs contacted recently retired QB [[Daunte Culpepper]] and free agent QB [[Bruce Gradkowski]].<ref name=\"change kickers\"/> Culpepper acted as his own agent and asked for \"preposterous\" contract terms, which caused many teams to cancel talks, including Kansas City.<ref name=\"Culpepper drops\">{{cite web|title=Sources: Culpepper drops visit with Chiefs |url=http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8728262/Sources:-Culpepper-drops-visit-with-Chiefs |last=Glazer |first=Jay |work=Fox Sports |date=October 28, 2008 |accessdate=October 28, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081031081808/http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8728262/Sources%3A-Culpepper-drops-visit-with-Chiefs |archivedate=October 31, 2008 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref> Culpepper agreed to meet with the Chiefs on October 28 for a physical and face-to-face negotiations but canceled the meeting in favor of other opportunities with the NFL.<ref name=\"Culpepper drops\"/>\n\n===Jared Allen trade===\n\nIn February, the Chiefs placed the franchise tag on DE [[Jared Allen]] to prevent him from hitting the free agent market before the teams agree on a long-term deal.<ref name=\"tag on Allen\"/> In April, reports surfaced detailing a proposed trade between Kansas City and the [[Minnesota Vikings]] which would send Allen to Minnesota in exchange for additional selections in the [[2008 NFL Draft]].<ref name=\"Chiefs keeping options\">Associated Press. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3353557 Chiefs keeping options open with Pro Bowl end Allen] ''ESPN.com'', April 18, 2008.</ref> Other teams that had contacted Allen's agent include the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] and the [[Jacksonville Jaguars]].<ref name=\"Glazer, Allen\">Glazer, Jay. [http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8043460/Chiefs'-Allen-talking-with-Vikings,-Bucs Chiefs' Allen talking with Vikings, Bucs]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080420224337/http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8043460/Chiefs%27-Allen-talking-with-Vikings%2C-Bucs |date=April 20, 2008 }} ''Fox Sports'', April 17, 2008.</ref> The [[Philadelphia Eagles]] also proposed a trade with Kansas City.<ref name=\"Eagles trade\">Smith, Michael David. [http://sports.aol.com/fanhouse/2008/04/22/could-eagles-trade-for-chiefs-jared-allen/ Could Eagles trade for Chiefs' Jared Allen?] ''AOL Sports'', April 22, 2008.</ref> Allen was not tagged as an exclusive rights franchise player and had the right to visit and negotiate with other teams.<ref name=\"Status of DE\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/17/chiefs_statement_on_the_status_of_de_jared_allen/ Chiefs statement on the status of DE Jared Allen] ''KCChiefs.com'', April 17, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080420215613/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/17/chiefs_statement_on_the_status_of_de_jared_allen/ |date=April 20, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nChiefs [[general manager]] [[Carl Peterson]]'s relationship with Allen had been strained ever since Peterson, in the wake of Allen's [[Drunk driving (United States)|DUI]] convictions, described him as \"a young man at risk.\"<ref name=\"Chiefs keeping options\"/> Allen, who could be suspended for a season if he has another alcohol-related episode, had said he would not negotiate with Kansas City if he did not get a contract done by July 2009.<ref name=\"Chiefs keeping options\"/> Allen had previously voiced his wish to stay with the Chiefs.<ref name=\"tag on Allen\"/>\n\nOn April 22, the Chiefs and Vikings reached an agreement on a trade package, and at roughly the same time, Allen reached an agreement in principle on a contract with the Vikings. Upon reaching the contract agreement, Allen headed to the airport and left for Minnesota.<ref name=\"Allen to Vikes\">Clayton, John. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3362701 Sources: Chiefs agree to send franchise player Allen to Vikes] ''ESPN.com'', April 22, 2008.</ref>\n\nSources said the Vikings included a second third-round pick (No. 73) in the 2008 draft to get the deal done. They had been offering a No. 1 pick (17th in the first round) and a No. 3 (No. 82). The teams also swapped spots in the sixth round with the Vikings getting a better spot in the sixth round, sources said.<ref name=\"Allen to Vikes\"/>\n\n===2008 NFL Draft===\nThe Chiefs chose fifth overall in the [[2008 NFL Draft]].<ref name=\"Chiefs secure\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/02/22/chiefs_secure_fifth_overall_selection_in_2008_nfl_draft/ Chiefs secure fifth overall selection in 2008 NFL Draft] ''KCChiefs.com'', February 22, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080225232831/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/02/22/chiefs_secure_fifth_overall_selection_in_2008_nfl_draft/ |date=February 25, 2008 }}</ref> A coin flip held at the [[NFL Scouting Combine]] determined the tie-breaker between the Chiefs, Falcons, and Raiders.<ref>Associated Press. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3175275 Raiders, Falcons, Chiefs to decide draft order with coin flip] ''ESPN.com'', December 31, 2007.</ref> The Chiefs had a league-high 13 selections heading into the draft.<ref name=\"KC trades DE Jared Allen\">[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/23/kc_trades_de_jared_allen_to_minnesota_for_multiple_draft_choices/ KC trades DE Jared Allen to Minnesota for multiple draft choices] ''KCChiefs.com'', April 23, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501130535/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/04/23/kc_trades_de_jared_allen_to_minnesota_for_multiple_draft_choices/ |date=May 1, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nKansas City was interested in [[defensive end]] [[Chris Long (American football)|Chris Long]] following the departure of [[Jared Allen]], but ended up with [[Glenn Dorsey]] after he slipped to #5 overall. Kansas City had Dorsey rated higher than Long,<ref name=\"Draft grades\">Czarnecki, John. [http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8079910/Handing-out-draft-grades-for-AFC-teams Handing our draft grades for AFC teams] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501031816/http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/8079910/Handing-out-draft-grades-for-AFC-teams |date=May 1, 2008 }} ''Fox Sports'', April 27, 2008.</ref> despite not having an immediate need at the position. Regardless of concern from NFL scouts about a previous leg injury to Dorsey which may cause him to get surgery in the near future, Kansas City selected Dorsey fifth overall.<ref name=\"Draft grades\"/> Dorsey and OT [[Branden Albert]], Kansas City's other first-round selection, were considered by some to be the best players in the entire Draft.<ref name=\"Several '08\"/><ref name=\"Chiefs' Day 1\"/><ref name=\"Draft yields\"/>\n\nSeveral analysts considered Kansas City to have made the best draft selections of any team.<ref name=\"Several '08\"/><ref name=\"Draft grades\"/><ref name=\"Chiefs' Day 1\">[[John Clayton (sportswriter)|Clayton, John.]] [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/draft08/columns/story?columnist=clayton_john&id=3369696 Chiefs' Day 1 plan comes together with Dorsey, others] ''ESPN.com'', April 26, 2008.</ref><ref name=\"Draft yields\">[[Mel Kiper, Jr.|Kiper, Jr., Mel.]] [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/draft08/columns/story?columnist=kiper_jr_mel&id=3357479 Draft yields quantity, and plenty of quality, for Chiefs] ''ESPN.com'', April 27, 2008.</ref><ref name=\"Chiefs benefit\">Williamson, Bill. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/draft08/columns/story?columnist=williamson_bill&id=3370625 AFC West: Chiefs benefit from Dorsey's slight fall] ''ESPN.com'', April 27, 2008.</ref><ref name=\"Chiefs, Cowboys shine\">McClain, John. [http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/sports/5733550.html Chiefs, Cowboys shine] ''Houston Chronicle'', April 27, 2008.</ref><ref name=\"Making sense\">{{cite news|first=Peter |last=King |authorlink=Peter King (sportswriter) |title=Monday Morning QB: Making sense of the 2008 NFL draft |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2008/writers/peter_king/04/27/mmqb.draft/index.html |work=Sports Illustrated |date=April 28, 2008 |accessdate=December 15, 2008  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081101193118/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2008/writers/peter_king/04/27/mmqb.draft/index.html |archivedate=November 1, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref><ref name=\"rookie pool\">Clayton, John. [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3385956 Chiefs get largest rookie pool to pay draft picks] ''ESPN.com'', May 7, 2008.</ref> Kansas City also received the largest rookie pool to pay their 12 rookies, with a sum of US$8,221,790, due in part to their two selections in the top 15 of the NFL Draft.<ref name=\"rookie pool\"/>\n\n[[File:Glenn Dorsey-LSU.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Kansas City selected [[Glenn Dorsey]] fifth overall in the [[2008 NFL Draft]] to help improve their defensive line.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Round\n!Selection\n!Name\n!Position\n!College\n!Contract\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |1\n|5\n|[[Glenn Dorsey]]\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|[[LSU Tigers football|Louisiana State]]\n|Six years<ref>[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/26/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_firstround_pick_dt_glenn_dorsey/ Chiefs agree to terms with first round pick DT Glenn Dorsey] ''KCChiefs.com'', July 26, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080728232743/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/26/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_firstround_pick_dt_glenn_dorsey/ |date=July 28, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n|15{{Ref label|Minnesota|a|a}}{{Ref label|Detroit|e|e}}\n|[[Branden Albert]]\n|[[Offensive lineman|Guard]]\n|[[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]\n|Five years<ref>[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/24/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_t_branden_albert/ Chiefs agree to terms with T Branden Albert] ''KCChiefs.com'', July 24, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080726053656/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/24/chiefs_agree_to_terms_with_t_branden_albert/ |date=July 26, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n|2\n|35\n|[[Brandon Flowers (American football)|Brandon Flowers]]\n|[[Defensive back|Cornerback]]\n|[[Virginia Tech Hokies football|Virginia Tech]]\n|Four years<ref>[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/23/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_cb_brandon_flowers/ Kansas City agrees to terms with CB Brandon Flowers] ''KCChiefs.com'', July 23, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080726153848/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/07/23/kansas_city_agrees_to_terms_with_cb_brandon_flowers/ |date=July 26, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |3\n|73{{Ref label|Detroit|e|e}}\n|[[Jamaal Char