\u2013 [[David Gibbs (football coach)|David Gibbs]]\n* Defensive Assistant/Assistant Linebackers \u2013 [[Michael Ketchum]]\n* Defensive Quality Control \u2013 [[Daron Roberts]]\n\n'''Special Teams Coaches'''\n* Special Teams Coordinator \u2013 [[Mike Priefer]]\n\n'''Strength and Conditioning'''\n* Strength and Conditioning \u2013 [[Cedric Smith (American football)|Cedric Smith]]\n* Assistant Strength and Conditioning \u2013 [[Brent Salazar]]\n* Player Development \u2013 [[Nate Wainright]]\n|}\n\n==Pre-season==\n\n===Training camp===\nThe Chiefs departed for [[NFL Training Camp|training camp]] at the [[University of Wisconsin\u2013River Falls]] on July 24 and broke camp on August 15. The 2008 training camp session marked the Chiefs' 18th season in [[River Falls, Wisconsin]]. Prior to the start of the season, Kansas City named [[Patrick Surtain]], [[Pat Thomas (linebacker)|Pat Thomas]], [[Brian Waters]], and [[Jon McGraw]] as team captains.<ref>[http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/09/04/chiefs_elect_2008_season_captains__waters_thomas_surtain_mcgraw/ Chiefs elect 2008 season captains: Waters, Thomas, Surtain, McGraw] ''KCChiefs.com'', September 4, 2008.  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080907192415/http://kcchiefs.com/news/2008/09/04/chiefs_elect_2008_season_captains__waters_thomas_surtain_mcgraw/ |date=September 7, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n===Exhibition games===\nThe Chiefs played the Chicago Bears on August 7 and their offense was very consistent. They won the game 24\u201320 and had their first victory in the pre-season since August 2006. The team lost to the [[Arizona Cardinals]] by a score of 27\u201317 at Arrowhead Stadium on August 16. The Chiefs were shut out by the [[Miami Dolphins]] at [[Dolphin Stadium]] by a score of 24\u20130 on August 23. Kansas City played its final pre-season game against the [[St. Louis Rams]] on August 28 at [[Arrowhead Stadium]] for the [[Governor's Cup (Missouri)|Missouri Governor's Cup]]. The Chiefs won the game 21\u201317.\n\n==Schedule==\n{{Cleanup rewrite|2=section|date=May 2019}}\nThe [[2008 NFL season]] schedule was released on April 15. The Chiefs were reportedly one of the four teams being considered to play an international regular season game in London in 2008. Among the Chiefs, the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]], [[New Orleans Saints]], and [[Seattle Seahawks]] were in consideration.<ref name=\"Sources: Bills\">[[Chris Mortensen|Mortensen, Chris.]] [http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=3205488 Sources: Bills likely to get OK to play game in Toronto] ''ESPN.com'', January 20, 2008.</ref> The Chargers and Saints were later chosen instead.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''''[[2008 Kansas City Chiefs season#Pre-season|Pre-season]]'''''\n|-\n! Week || Date || Opponent || Result || Kickoff || Game site || TV || Record || Match Report\n|-  style=\"background:#dfd; text-align:center;\"\n| 1 || August 7, 2008 || [[2008 Chicago Bears season|Chicago Bears]] || '''W''' 24\u201320 || 7:00&nbsp;PM [[Central Standard Time|CST]] || [[Soldier Field]] || [[KCTV]] || 1\u20130 || [https://web.archive.org/web/20080910044256/http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/recap?game_id=29788&displayPage=tab_recap&season=2008&week=PRE1 Recap]\n|-  style=\"background:#fdd; text-align:center;\"\n| 2 || August 16, 2008 || [[2008 Arizona Cardinals season|Arizona Cardinals]] || '''L''' 17\u201327 || 7:00&nbsp;PM CST || [[Arrowhead Stadium]] || KCTV || 1\u20131 || [https://web.archive.org/web/20080912134324/http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/recap?game_id=29807&displayPage=tab_recap&season=2008&week=PRE2 Recap]\n|-  style=\"background:#fdd; text-align:center;\"\n| 3 || August 23, 2008 || [[2008 Miami Dolphins season|Miami Dolphins]] || '''L''' 0\u201324 || 6:30&nbsp;PM CST || [[Dolphin Stadium]] || KCTV || 1\u20132 || [https://web.archive.org/web/20080912193732/http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/recap?game_id=29825&displayPage=tab_recap&season=2008&week=PRE3 Recap]\n|-  style=\"backgroun